    - target: {fileID: 5109087311396199045, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: plantData
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 362b03b67316ec546a90b40cad5cb837, type: 2}
    - target: {fileID: 5109087311396199045, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: scatterer
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 8931080370875138959}
    - target: {fileID: 5109087311396199045, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: selectionCollider
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 798614429097540612}
    - target: {fileID: 5122842465899161861, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "In May it rains\nFerns unfurls in light green color,\nBut when?\n\n\u2014
        Matsuo Basho"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5122842465899161861, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5431834928911583791, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Sprite
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 7453befaa862c7b4e9d911d98f0fd83d, type: 3}
    - target: {fileID: 5431834928911583797, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Sprite
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 54efa635c0a7e544f8b535bf50b4f11b, type: 3}
    - target: {fileID: 5902464882853280731, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: instanceId
      value: 19b92c50-e5a4-4105-925a-48c883ce50e6
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082410, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "K\u0101rlis Skalbe \u2014 _Papardes zieds_ (also known as _J\u0101\u0146u
        pasaka_, _Midsummer Tale_)\nLoose English:\n\n\"Let's go look for the fern
        flower,\" the boy said, and his breath caught. For the fern flower appeared
        only on J\u0101\u0146i night, a brief moment between evening's afterglow
        and morning's light, and whoever finds it is happy. \"Let's go,\" the girl
        whispered as quietly as the darkness in the forest. Hand in hand, they crept
        under the alder branches, still sweetly flushed from the evening sun\u2026
        Bending down, they groped with their hands through the forest darkness and
        parted the fern clumps. They found glow-worms there and placed them on each
        other's palms like drops of diamond. But the fern flower was not there. And
        somehow, as they bent among the bushes, they no longer sought the flower,
        but only each other's hands. They grew confused and stopped facing one another,
        close, close. Their breath met \u2014 and what a wonder \u2014 when lips
        drew near to lips, it was as though the fern flower had bloomed between them\u2026\""
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082410, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082416, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: 'Fern in Baltic Culture

        In baltic tradition the Ferns flower
        is essential to summer Solstice. Finding a flowering fern is said to come
        with wealth and knowledge, like abilities to talk to animals or read minds.
        The idea was that fern is so mystical that it only opens its flower on midnight
        of the longest day of the year.


        Further there are also romatic
        connotations. Young couples going to the forest alone to "look for the fern
        flower" was a euphemism for intimacy. This tradition was also a way to get
        around societal regulations on who to marry.'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082416, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 6181259333930047258, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: GsplatAsset
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 4599839170941234424, guid: 23e2f50798e222e46814ced506b347dd, type: 3}
    - target: {fileID: 6181259333930047258, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_assetGuid
      value: 23e2f50798e222e46814ced506b347dd
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 6835627233580907840, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Sprite
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 182840cef3134db4b8eefc2d6e80f7a3, type: 3}
    - target: {fileID: 7173199714940506848, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "The Author Bash\u014D was not yet Bash\u014D when he wrote it. He was
        T\u014Dsei, the unripe peach, watching a fern slowly unfurling. Ultimately
        asking the question of himself."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 7173199714940506848, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 7417057368276200879, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Sprite
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 21300000, guid: d857c9a39eafdd343955be0779df14e7, type: 3}
    - target: {fileID: 8810918796485297829, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Sprite
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 4770e91251e57104d82c76ef2a8c4e56, type: 3}
    - target: {fileID: 9161542878112791018, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "Ode to Bamboo \u2014 Huang Tingjian (Excerpt)\n\u8568\u82BD\u521D\u653E\u5C0F\u513F\u62F3\u3002\nFern
        buds barely unfurling \u2014 like a small child's fist."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9161542878112791018, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
